Get top-ranked names

top_ranked_names.Rd

Summarises and ranks names by count using either baseline or adjusted values.

Usage

top_ranked_names(
  data = a4syahpradana::common_names,
  type = c("first", "last"),
  measure = c("estimate", "final_estimate"),
  starts_with = NULL,
  n = 10
)

Arguments

data

Data frame, default is a4syahpradana::common_names

type

"first" for first names or "last" for surnames

measure

Either "estimate" or "final_estimate"

starts_with

Optional prefix to filter names (case-insensitive)

n

Number of top names to return

Value

A tibble with columns Name and Count.
